name: Joey Chestnut
summary: Competitive eater Joey Chestnut has been banned from participating in the iconic Nathan's Hot Dog Eating Contest on July 4th due to a sponsorship deal with Impossible Foods, a rival to Nathan's beef-based hot dogs. Chestnut, who holds the record for consuming the most hot dogs in the contest, is prohibited from competing in the 2024 event after striking a sponsorship agreement with Impossible Foods, which produces plant-based hot dogs. The move has sparked a rivalry between Chestnut and Nathan's, leading to the exclusion of the champion from the contest. Notably, Chestnut will face off against his former rival Takeru Kobayashi in a separate Labor Day hot dog eating contest on Netflix, highlighting the ongoing tension between the two competitive eaters.

name: iOS 18
summary: The latest developments in iOS 18 have been widely reported in the news. MacRumors outlines the anticipated features, compatible devices, and launch date, while Apple's official preview highlights the features coming to iPhones in the fall. CNET and TechRadar cover the confirmed features and predicted release date. iMore delves into the specifics of Apple Intelligence and ChatGPT integration on iOS 18. 9to5Mac provides details on the features included in the beta 1 release. USA TODAY covers the overall release, features, and changes in iOS 18. WIRED lists the most prominent new features coming to both iOS 18 and iPadOS 18. Variety reports on the latest iPhone software release, and ZDNet summaries the most significant changes announced at WWDC 2024.
